**Introduction**

The objective of this project is to implement a blade icing mitigation program to reduce production losses associated with severe icing events across seven Liberty Power (Liberty) wind farms located in the United States and Canada. The scope of work includes:â€‹

- Deployment of near real-time monitoring system for detecting severe icing events, integration of weather forecast and monitoring dashboards.â€‹
- Deployment of a syndicated and approved Operational Readiness Plan used to support the implementation of the Mitigation Program.â€‹
- Monitoring activities including weather forecasting, mitigation process deployment, event review, icing summaries and bi-weekly KPI tracking.â€‹

**_Deploy a blade icing mitigation program to reduce blade icing impacts, improve event forecasting and_** â€‹  
**_establish processes that allows for continuous improvement and knowledge sharing._**â€‹

&nbsp;**![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)**

**Backgroundâ€‹**

**The following work scope is a continuation of tasks identified in the blade icing diagnostic conducted for seven wind sites located in Canada and the United States. The diagnostic demonstrated moderate to excellent opportunity to mitigate blade icing impacts.** â€‹

**It is important to acknowledge that mitigation of severe icing events is a process that focuses on a risk reduction strategy by pausing turbines during critical periods to reduce ice accretion on blades.**â€‹

The intent of the mitigation program is to minimize blade icing impacts through the deployment of a standardized process that integrates site-specific analytics and decision criteria developed from historical icing events. These factors enable effective mitigation through:â€‹

- Improved near real-time monitoring and forecasting capabilities of forward-looking events.â€‹
- Site-specific operational readiness plans utilizing standardized procedures that provides appropriate direction.â€‹
- Design mechanisms that encourage the integration of new data (i.e., winter seasons) for continuous improvement.â€‹

**Context**

**The objective of this work scope is to deploy a successful Blade Icing Mitigation Program through the 2021/22 winter season. The program will provide Liberty with flexibility to adjust procedures and track Key Performance Indicators (KPIs), at a site level, to evaluate the effectiveness of the Mitigation Program. The ORP includes:**â€‹

- **Monitoring Applications:** Develop a near real-time icing monitoring system that integrate icing models with weather forecasts and site performance data including alarm management functionality. â€‹
- **Operational Readiness Plan:** Conduct change management activities through focused engagements with all stakeholders to solicit feedback and understand key concerns and/or site-specific requirements.â€‹
- **Remote Monitoring:** Define and establish key processes and actions required to execute mitigation procedures, including the deployment of a site-specific case-control design to track KPIs.â€‹
- **Program Deployment:** Establish stakeholder accountabilities and near real-time monitoring activities to effectively deploy and execute the Mitigation Program through the 2021/22 winter season.â€‹
